  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Currently the new state mgmt service is implemented as a wrapper on top of DB, it's implemented as a service because it does service-like thing (ie. replay blocks, execute state transitions) @prestonvanloon brought a good point the new mgmt service should be an implementation as DB for better UX.\r\n\r\nThe easier to reason DB is the universal way on how users access state throughout the application. With DB still public, having two ways to access states means that it could the code and logic complicated",
